      • addRpcImplementation

        public Broker.RpcRegistration addRpcImplementation(org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.common.QName rpcType,
                                          RpcImplementation implementation)
                                            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Deprecated. 
        Description copied from interface: RpcProvisionRegistry
        Registers an implementation of the rpc.

        The registered rpc functionality will be available to all other consumers and providers registered to the broker, which are aware of the QName assigned to the rpc.

        There is no assumption that rpc type is in the set returned by invoking RpcImplementation.getSupportedRpcs(). This allows for dynamic rpc implementations.

        Specified by:
        addRpcImplementation in interface RpcProvisionRegistry
        Parameters:
        rpcType - Name of Rpc
        implementation - Provider's Implementation of the RPC functionality
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the name of RPC is invalid
